When calling
```c
if (call_soon(state, fut->fut_loop, cb, (PyObject *)fut, ctx))
```
in the callback-iteration loop, we must `Py_INCREF(fut)` before calling, and `Py_DECREF(fut)` immediately after. Otherwise, if any of these callbacks can cause `fut` to be deallocated (by clearing e.g. a container holding it), then `call_soon` will have a stack pointer to a freed PyObject, causing use-after-free once the Python machinery tries to manipulate it as a live object.

The original attempt only covered the first callback, but not all subsequent calls inside the callbacks loop.

